       global,  the  command line argument vector.  list of valid
       single-letter options.

   GGlloobbaallss
       Tcl command line argument vector Tcl list index in argv of
       next  argument to be processed.  Tcl list index in argv of
       option argument.  boolean  controlling  error  message  on
       stderr. Defaults to 1.  Set to 0 to suppress.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       The  next  valid option letter from argv. ? for an invalid
       option or missing option argument. ``-1'' when all command
       line  options  have  been  parsed.   optarg  points to the
       option argument if the returned option letter  takes  such
       and argument and it is present in argv.

       optind is left pointing to the next argument in argv.

